ess.=E2=80=9D For instance, she wrote, =E2=80=9Ccrypto is back again, and t=
his time around, almost nobody is pretending the endeavor is about anything=
 other than =E2=80=98number go up.=E2=80=99=E2=80=9D I quibbled:
Well, everyone is=C2=A0pretending. =E2=80=A6 That=E2=80=99s what=E2=80=99s =
so weird about all of this.=C2=A0If you are a meme-stock executive or a cry=
pto venture capitalist or Robinhood, you can=E2=80=99t just go on TV and sa=
y =E2=80=9Cyes gambling is fun and legal and we are probabilistically charg=
ing people a market-clearing price for entertainment.=E2=80=9D You have to =
talk about how your meme stock is the future of free speech or how crypto i=
